                  , Nemini loquentes verbum. So verſ. 20, Loquebantur ad Graecos, They ſpake unto the Graecians. The ſame word is uſed in Epheſ. 4.25, Loquimini quiſque veritatem proximo ſuo: Speak every man truth with his neighbour.
